<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN"
    "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Vibe Bar runs unsandboxed on purpose.

        The misc-providers integration needs to read other browsers'
        cookie SQLite databases (Chromium Safe Storage decrypt via
        Keychain) and shell out to lsof / ps to discover the
        AntiGravity language-server port and CSRF token. Both
        capabilities are blocked by `com.apple.security.app-sandbox`,
        so the sandbox is intentionally absent.

        See AGENTS.md § 6 for the full reasoning, the trade-offs, and
        the steps to re-enable the sandbox if a future requirement
        (e.g. Mac App Store distribution) ever changes the calculus.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
